<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="143" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1504,2036]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">
—A Balkan endemic, present in 
<collectingCountry box="[992,1088,1756,1781]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1109,1286,1756,1781]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref7819" refString="Abadjiev, S. (2001) An Atlas of the Distribution of the Butterflies in Bulgaria (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea &amp; Papilionoidea). Pensoft Publishers, Sofia-Moscow, 335 pp." type="book">Abadjiev 2001</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1312,1437,1756,1781]" name="Macedonia" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">
<collectingRegion box="[1312,1437,1756,1781]" country="Greece" name="Dytiki Makedonia" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">Macedonia</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[158,335,1792,1817]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref9990" refString="Melovski, D. (2002) Daily butterflies (Rhopalocera) on Sar Planina Mt. Bulletin of the Biology Students' Research Society, 2, 131 - 144." type="journal article">Melovski 2002</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[357,429,1792,1817]" name="Serbia" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">Serbia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[446,653,1792,1817]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref9095" refString="Jaksic, P., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Petrovic, S. (2013) Compendium of Serbian Butterflies with vernacular names. Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, 6, 75 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.5937 / bnhmb 1306075 J" type="journal article">
Jakšić 
<emphasis box="[525,584,1792,1817]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[675,764,1792,1817]" name="Albania" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">Albania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[780,1085,1792,1817]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref10368" refString="Popovic, M., Duric, M., Franeta, F. &amp; Verovnik, R. (2013) On the extremely rich butterfly fauna (Lepidoptera: Rhopalocera) on the soth-eastern foothills of Stara Planina Mts in Serbia. Phegea, 41 (4), 74 - 81." type="journal article">Verovnik &amp; Popović 2013</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1152,1231,1792,1816]" name="Greece" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">Greece</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1248,1425,1792,1817]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref10255" refString="Pamperis, L. (2009) Butterflies of Greece (Second edition). Pamperis, Athens, 766 pp." type="book">Pamperis 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The species was recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[494,631,1829,1853]" name="Serbia" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
from the Čakor mountain pass, on the Prokletije mountains (
<bibRefCitation pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref9007" refString="Jaksic, P. &amp; Pesic, B. (1995) The distribution of certain Erebia species in Serbia (Lepidoptera, Satyridae). [Rasprostranjenje nekih Erebia vrsta u Srbiji (Lepidoptera, Satyridae)]. Univerzitetska misao, 2 (1), 23 - 26." type="journal article">Jakšić &amp; Pešić 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[300,440,1864,1889]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref8859" refString="Jaksic, P. (2001) The distribution of Erebia rhodopensis Nicholl, 1900 (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae, Satyrinae) on the Sar- Planina, Prokletije and Rila. Entomologist's Gazette, 52, 83 - 90." type="journal article">Jakšić 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[458,532,1864,1889]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref8940" refString="Jaksic, P. (2003 b) Fauna leptira (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae, Hesperioidea i Papilionoidea) metohijskih Prokletija. In: Amidzic, L., Jankovic, M. M. &amp; Jaksic, P. (Eds.), Metohijske Prokletije, prirodna i kulturna bastina. Zavod za zastitu prirode Srbije, Beograd, pp. 234 - 261." type="book chapter">2003b</bibRefCitation>
). The author in the company of Martin Gascoigne-Pees observed one male specimen on Mt. Bogićevica in the Prokletije mountain range on 
<date box="[881,1041,1899,1927]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" value="2017-07-12">July 12th 2017</date>
.
</paragraph>
